species (living in the deepest parts of the marsh), heron diet was very similar to fish species composition
of the community occurring in the marsh. The catfish was the species captured most frequently by
the heron (45 \% of the ma\ss), the eel was second with 28 \% of the ma\ss. The catfish was probably over
represented in the diet considering that they are caught in catfish-dumps created by profe\ssional fishermen at Grand-Lieu lake, in order to reduce the density of this undesirable species. Inversely, small species
such as Gasterosteus aculeatus were not found in the diet whereas they are very numerous in the marsh.
On average herons of Grand-Lieu colony catch 1.92 kg of fish per ha of marsh (6\% of the fish standing
crops in the marsh) during the breeding season, the main predation period.},
